Description: Limestone ostracon: on one side only, eight lines of a text concerning deliveries of various articles and - separated from this enumeration by a line - six lines of another practically unintelligible text. On one edge faint traces of a line of text.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: S. Birch, 'Inscriptions in the Hieratic and Demotic Character, from the Collections of the British Museum' (London l868), pl. XIX; J. J. Černy and A.H. Gardiner, ‘Hieratic Ostraca’ (Oxford 1957), p. 23 and pl. LXXXVII, 2.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (136352) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/136352)
Condition: Fair but worn, upper right edge flaked off.
